The paper deals with the estimation of complexity of images and their classification based on their information content. This involves the use of mathematical concepts such as logical depth and Kolmogorov complexity, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also involves the analysis of visual representations of images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper involves the use of classification techniques, which is a common topic in data science (cs.DS).
